=head2 C<l0x1-hello_world>: A bare "Hello World" partition.

I<This example explains how to build a "Hello world" partition using the XAL layer.>

=head3 Partition definition:

This example is composed of one XAL bare partition that prints "Hello World!"
to the partition console device configured in the file C<xm_cf.ia32.xml>.
The code run by the partition can be found in the file C<hello.c>.

Termination: After printing "Hello World!" the partition terminates (Halt partition). 

=head3 Configuration table:

Basic configuration.
Partitions are defined to be executed at different memory addresses.
P1 is defined as supervisor.

A scheduling plan is defined under the following premises:

    MAF = 1000 msec
    P1: S   0 ms  D 500 ms  

=head3 Expected results:

XtratuM will load, initialise and run in user mode the partitions. 
During the execution, partitions will print "Hello World!" and halt.

